post_text:
August 24, 2020 - Today, the Slater School Board of Education decided to delay the start of school to Tuesday, September 1, 2020. Due to the increase rise of COVID cases in our area, it is in the best interest for our Wildcat Family to do so at this time.
All face-to-face activities and practices are suspended until Tuesday, Sept. 1, 2020, although virtual practices may still take place.
We will continue to evaluate the situation to keep our community informed. As of now, classes will begin Sept. 1 whether that be online or face-to-face with decisions to be released on Friday, Aug. 28, 2020.
